
[1]sabellian

   SABELLIAN, a. Pertaining to the heresy of Sabellius.

   SABELLIAN, n. A follower of Sabellius, a philosopher of Egypt in the
   third century, who openly taught that there is one person only in the
   Godhead, and that the Word and Holy Spirit are only virtues, emanations
   or functions of the Deity.
